   +pod('The Mystery of Kuru')
      .uk-width-medium-6-10
         p
            | In the 1950s, a district medical officer working in the highlands of New Guinea
            | observed a fatal disease among the people of the Fore (FOR-ay) tribe. The Fore
            | people called this sickness kuru, which means &quot;trembling in fear.&quot; After intially
            | becoming unable to walk, victims of kuru lost the ability to swallow or chew.
            | Drastic weight loss would inevitably lead to death. Today we know that kuru is
            | one of several diseases in humans and animals caused by prion (PREE-on) proteins.

      .uk-width-medium-4-10.uk-text-center
         figure
            img.lg-no-shadow(src='images/new-guinea-map.jpg', alt='New Guinea')

      .uk-width-1-1
         +toggle ('More about Kuru...')
            include kuru


